# Create Website
@divider

When creating your site, it's important to understand the key files and how they work together. This page walks through the basics of setting up a Marque project, including the file structure, key configuration files, and recommended editing order.

## Create a project
@divider

@row
  @card .primary
    ## Create and serve
    @divider

    Using the Marque CLI, you can create a new project with a single command. This includes some example content to get you started.

    ```sh
    marque new my-site
    cd my-site
    marque serve .
    ```

    You can pick a layout and theme upfront if you already know what you want:

    ```sh
    marque new my-site --layout topnav --theme rustique
    ```
  @end card

  @card
    ## Project structure
    @divider

      The project has a simple structure. The `my-site/` directory contains your source files, while the `dist/` directory is generated when you build or serve the site.

    ```txt
    my-site/
    ├── directives/   # custom directives, loaded on build and serve
    ├── layouts/      # HTML shell and layout CSS
    ├── pages/        # .mq source files
    ├── static/       # copied as-is to output
    ├── themes/       # visual styling
    ├── marque.toml   # site-wide defaults
    └── summary.mq    # navigation structure
    ```

    `dist/` is generated when you run `marque build` or `marque serve`.
  @end card
@end row

@card
  ## Key files
  @divider

  @row

    @card
      Marque project require a two key files to function properly:
    
      - [`marque.toml`](docs/configuration/frontmatter.mq) defines the default configuration for your site, also known as [frontmatter](docs/configuration/frontmatter.mq).
      - [`summary.mq`](docs/configuration/summary.mq) defines the order and structure of the navigation menu, as well as the labels for each page.
    @end card
    
    @card
      The layout of a Marque project is:

    @end card

  @end row

@end card
