@row
  @card .primary
    ## `marque.toml`
    @divider
    Site-wide defaults: title, description, layout, theme, width, and alignment.

    If it should apply everywhere, set it here.
  @end card

  @card .secondary
    ## `summary.mq`
    @divider
    Navigation labels, order, grouping, and nesting.

    If it should appear in the menu, it needs an entry here.
  @end card
@end row

@row
  @card
    ## `pages/`
    @divider
    Each `.mq` file becomes a page. Start here.

    ```mq
    +++
    title = My Page
    nav = my-page
    +++

    # My Page
    ```
  @end card

  @card
    ## `directives/`, `themes/`, `layouts/`
    @divider
    Leave these alone until the content structure is settled.

    - `directives/`: custom authoring blocks
    - `themes/`: colours, type, and spacing
    - `layouts/`: page shell and nav placement
  @end card
@end row

@callout .info
A page in `pages/` won't appear in the menu unless it has an entry in `summary.mq`.
@end callout

## Edit in this order
@divider

@card
@container
  @step
  Set the site title, layout, theme, and alignment in `marque.toml`.
  @end step

  @step
  Update `summary.mq` to match the navigation you actually want.
  @end step

  @step
  Replace or remove the starter pages in `pages/`.
  @end step

  @step
  Adjust `themes/`, `layouts/`, and `directives/` once the content structure is clear.
  @end step
@end container
@end card

## Defaults and overrides
@divider

@row
  @card
    ## Site-wide vs per-page
    @divider
    Shared decisions go in `marque.toml`.
    One-off decisions go in page frontmatter.
  @end card

  @card
    ## Source vs output
    @divider
    Edit everything except `dist/`.
    Treat `dist/` as disposable — it is regenerated on every build.
  @end card
@end row

